      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne, ¶ 28/7/84 ¶ T. R. Wilson Esqr. ¶ Undersecretary. ¶ Sir...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">84.07.28</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Thomas Wilson</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">A84/6221, unit 51, VPRS 3992/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">28/7/84</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">T. R. Wilson Esqr.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Undersecretary.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In the letter, which three days ago I had the honor to forward to the hon. the Chief Secretary concerning Junior Assistant Henry,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to G. Berry, 25 July 1884 (in this edition as 84-07-25a).</p>
               </note> I have made a mistake by stating, that he had been <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">two</hi>
               </seg> years in the service of the Government, trusting to <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">his own statement</hi>
               </seg> as correct; but on referring to the books of the office I find, that he was fully <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">three</hi>
               </seg> years in Governments employ, so that if the honorable the Chief Secretary would kindly grant him a gratuity at the rate of service, it would be for three not two years.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The file contains a sheet in an unknown hand: 'Henry is not under the Civil Service Act — he has been paid out of the vote for Contingencies viz XXX Wages of Junior Assistants &amp;c"</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 1.3193in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Date of entry <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>1st July 1881 —</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 1.3193in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Age<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>34 years</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 1.3193in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Rate of pay <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>7/6d per diem —</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.9862in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                     xml:lang="en">If he be incapacitated by bodily infirmity from the discharge of his duty, he can receive a gratuity, but only by a vote of the House</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 1.3193in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; "
                     xml:lang="en">1/8 —</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by Wilson, 14 August: "Inf[or]m Govt Botanist that resig[natio]n of Mr Henry will be accepted but that no gratuity can be given'. See T. Wilson to M, 19 August 1884 (in this edition as 84-08-19a).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <seg style="">Sir, your obedient servant</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
